<!-- 
	Filters!in
		Dry=On
		Rain=On
		Snow=On
		
		Day=On
		Night=On
		
		Spring=On
		Summer=On
		Autumn=On
		Winter=On
		
		Burning=On
		Burning=Off

	Shaders!
		billboard
			Aligns an object to the camera, but not along the y axis.
			Used for trees. No reason it is limited to that use though.
			Diffuse texture only.

		night_glow
			Unlit object that just outputs vertex colour, multiplied up a little.
			
		night_glow_texture
			Unlit object that just outputs texture, multiplied up a little.
			
		standard
			Specifies a texture name, diffuse, normal and gloss maps are derived from this.
				
		standard_animated
			Specifies a texture name, diffuse, normal and gloss maps are derived from this.
				
		standard_with_alpha_test
			As the standard shader, only with an alpha test.
			
		standard_ambient
			As the standard shader, only with an additional ambient map applied.
			Ambient map specified by a seperate texture name to the diffuse/normal/gloss base.

		standard_simple
			Specifies a texture name, diffuse map is derived from this.
			
		vertex_wind
			As the standard shader, only vertices are procedurally moved by wind in the vertex shader.
			
		non_renderable
			Dummy used to specify an attach point in a model.
			
		burning_texture
			AKA burning panel.
			Specifies a texture name, diffuse, normal and gloss maps are derived from this.
			
		burning_vertex_alpha
			AKA burning frame.
			Specifies a texture name, diffuse, normal and gloss maps are derived from this.
			
		rain
			AKA roof rain shader.
			Specifies a texture name, diffuse, normal and gloss maps are derived from this.
			
		rain_skirt
			Parameters specified in code.
			
		point_light
			Puts a point light in the model, light is specified by a name used to look up in light.xml
			
		campaign_trees
			Diffuse texture only, but has seasonal variants.
			In game has no rotation, only position and scale.
			Fakes movement by animating normals in vertex shader to avoid nasty aliasing artifacts.
			
		grass
			Diffuse texture only.

		texture_combo_vertex_wind
		texture_combo
			These two are driven by code at run time. Used for the ui flags.
			
		decal_parallax
		decal_normal
		decal_offset_height
		decal_environment
		decal_waterfall
			I believe these are dummies used by the terrain system and can be ignored and never used.
			
		bow_wave
			All variables hard coded. Used for the wake on ships. Shouldn't use used in this document.
			
		tree
			AKA Trunk/Branch shader. Weighted and not currently supported.
			
		tree_leaf
			AKA Leaf shader. Weighted and not currently supported.
		
    cloth
      Cloth Shader
      
	Example shader:
	<LIGHTING_MATERIAL material_name = 'standard' filters = 'Rain=On;Snow=On' two_sided = 'true' alpha_blend = 'false'/>

 version_number attribute on the RIGID_MATERIAL tag must match the LIGHTING_MATERIALS_XML_VERSION_NUMBER value defined in Tooldatabuilder (RigidModel_v2.cpp)
-->

